11#ifndef MODULES_UTILITY_SOURCE_PROCESS_THREAD_IMPL_H_
12#define MODULES_UTILITY_SOURCE_PROCESS_THREAD_IMPL_H_
13
14#include <stdint.h>
15
16#include <list>
17#include <memory>
18#include <queue>
19
20#include "api/sequence_checker.h"
21#include "api/task_queue/queued_task.h"
22#include "modules/include/module.h"
23#include "modules/utility/include/process_thread.h"
24#include "rtc_base/deprecated/recursive_critical_section.h"
25#include "rtc_base/event.h"
26#include "rtc_base/location.h"
27#include "rtc_base/platform_thread.h"
28
29namespace webrtc {
30
31class ProcessThreadImpl : public ProcessThread {
32 public:
33 explicit ProcessThreadImpl(const char* thread_name);
34 ~ProcessThreadImpl() override;
35
36 void Start() override;
37 void Stop() override;
38
39 void WakeUp(Module* module) override;
40 void PostTask(std::unique_ptr<QueuedTask> task) override;
41 void PostDelayedTask(std::unique_ptr<QueuedTask> task,
42 uint32_t milliseconds) override;
43
44 void RegisterModule(Module* module, const rtc::Location& from) override;
45 void DeRegisterModule(Module* module) override;
46
47 protected:
48 bool Process();
49
50 private:
51 struct ModuleCallback {
52 ModuleCallback() = delete;
53 ModuleCallback(ModuleCallback&& cb) = default;
54 ModuleCallback(const ModuleCallback& cb) = default;
55 ModuleCallback(Module* module, const rtc::Location& location)
56 : module(module), location(location) {}
57 bool operator==(const ModuleCallback& cb) const {
58 return cb.module == module;
59 }
60
61 Module* const module;
62 int64_t next_callback = 0; // Absolute timestamp.
63 const rtc::Location location;
64
65 private:
66 ModuleCallback& operator=(ModuleCallback&);
67 };
68 struct DelayedTask {
69 DelayedTask(int64_t run_at_ms, std::unique_ptr<QueuedTask> task)
70 : run_at_ms(run_at_ms), task(task.release()) {}
71 friend bool operator<(const DelayedTask& lhs, const DelayedTask& rhs) {
72 // Earliest DelayedTask should be at the top of the priority queue.
73 return lhs.run_at_ms > rhs.run_at_ms;
74 }
75
76 int64_t run_at_ms;
77 // DelayedTask owns the |task|, but some delayed tasks must be removed from
78 // the std::priority_queue, but mustn't be deleted. std::priority_queue does
79 // not give non-const access to the values, so storing unique_ptr would
80 // delete the task as soon as it is remove from the priority queue.
81 // Thus lifetime of the |task| is managed manually.
82 QueuedTask* task;
83 };
84 typedef std::list<ModuleCallback> ModuleList;
85
86 void Delete() override;
87 // The part of Stop processing that doesn't need any locking.
88 void StopNoLocks();
89 void WakeUpNoLocks(Module* module);
90 void WakeUpInternal(Module* module) RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_);
91
92 // Members protected by this mutex are accessed on the constructor thread and
93 // on the spawned process thread, and locking is needed only while the process
94 // thread is running.
95 Mutex mutex_;
96
97 SequenceChecker thread_checker_;
98 rtc::Event wake_up_;
99 rtc::PlatformThread thread_;
100
101 ModuleList modules_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
102 // Set to true when calling Process, to allow reentrant calls to WakeUp.
103 bool holds_mutex_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(this) = false;
104 std::queue<QueuedTask*> queue_;
105 std::priority_queue<DelayedTask> delayed_tasks_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
106 // The `stop_` flag is modified only by the construction thread, protected by
107 // `thread_checker_`. It is read also by the spawned `thread_`. The latter
108 // thread must take `mutex_` before access, and for thread safety, the
109 // constructor thread needs to take `mutex_` when it modifies `stop_` and
110 // `thread_` is running. Annotations like RTC_GUARDED_BY doesn't support this
111 // usage pattern.
112 bool stop_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
113 const char* thread_name_;
114};
115
116} // namespace webrtc
117
118#endif // MODULES_UTILITY_SOURCE_PROCESS_THREAD_IMPL_H_
